Description: Tetris-like terminal game written in pure bash
 rowhammer is a Tetris-like game that runs entirely in the terminal and
 is modeled after "The New Tetris" (N64). It offers a classic 10x20
 board, the seven standard tetrominoes with a 7-bag randomizer, gravity
 with a level-based speed curve, line clearing, soft/hard drop, pause
 and restart, plus a start menu with configurable key bindings and
 player name.
 .
 The square system (gold/silver bonus blocks), the persistent wonders
 building mode and network multiplayer are planned for later releases.
 .
 The name is a pun on hammering rows of blocks; the game is unrelated
 to the hardware attack of the same name.
